items.text: At Symmetry, friendliness is so 80s. The food's pretty good but don't expect to feel welcomed.
The waitresses are hawt. No joke.
They have vanilla milkshake!!
Food is good but seriously over priced.
Very slow service, pseudo-creative menu averagely executed. They've very aware and friendly about their deficiencies though.
Great brunch dishes that are super Instagrammable (apart from choosing the white tables outdoors)
Cool, hip, beautiful décor and good food. I love this place!
It's probably time for them to change the menu, getting bored with the food.
The big breakfast is awesome! Try the mushrooms and the sausage!
Corned beef hash was good (though serving size was not generous), as were the waffles. Unfortunately coffee was a let-down; my expresso lacked flavour. Will return for the food but not the coffee
A hipster resto cafe, feels like the kind you see in hip parts of London. Delicious breakfast and brunch options with carefully-made coffee.
Truffles fries, cod carbonara must order
The ambience, food and coffee are great, though it is quite pricey!
Prices are abit high but wonderful food. Recommended by very helpful staff: Beef cheek and duck leg. Tried the beef cheek and it was plain awesome! Good portion, can share for 2, Mocha is a must try.
Nice pork croissant and beer
I have no idea why they insist on putting some kind of truffle aroma on their French fries but the serving is huge and comes with mayonnaise which makes this Dutch guy very happy.
Symmetry is one of those cafés which has good coffee AND good food. I had the Flan, an unassuming item tucked away at the corner of the menu, but don't be mistaken by the simple name - it's yummy!
Pretty pricey but the food and drinks are good. Try the squid with black pepper squid ink sauce, avoid the truffle fries
Limited snack menu until 6 pm, so if you're an early customer, forget about it
Awesome food - Ordered ham and mushroom padini! It was delicious! Truffle fries were awesome with the sauce! Little Creature bright ale taste good,likewise the coffee too!
Average tasted.. Over price food.. Good ambience.
The seats under the aircon is very cold, wish they would do something about it. Other than that nice place to chill out and enjoy the food. Love their truffle fries!
Love the smoothies!
Very nice place for weekend brunch. Making a reservation advised as it is usually crowded
Food was great and service staff was attentive. Would return for brunch again :) oh a little note, tone down the music.
Truffle fries were damn good. They call it Potato fries though.
Service was great with friendly staff! Brunch food was a bit of a disappointment. Hickory corned beef and sur le plat was just average
Cosy place with kwerky decors and nice coffees !
Atmosphere& tasty food and drink. I has benefit eggs and lichi lemonade
Croissant with Pork Belly Scrambled Eggs
Reconstructed lemon tart and avocado smoothie were damn good. Very trendy place but not cheap.
Ham hock and pancetta steak with scrambled eggs and soubise sauce. The ultimate lunch.
Eggs-cellent! The pork belly scrambled eggs croissant was very good. Coffee was good as well.
All staff are super approachable and friendly. Its like the place to really kick off your shoes and chill! :)
Brunch menu only for weekends - and really good. Love their interpretation of their eggs Ben, with portobello mushrooms. Yum.
Whenever I come back I remember why I left disappointed the last time. Nothing is terrible but it's all a little bit off. Too expensive, bad service (half an hour for a sandwich?!), average food.
Best brunch in SG! Just a bit too noisy with the sound trapped within the space.
2nd place (other than Jimmy Monkey) that I've been to with a Slayer coffee machine. Rustic appeal accompanied with great coffee & savory eggs ben to kick start the awesome weekends (;
Nice food and friendly service, the atmosphere is cozy and I like their music.
Dinner menu on weekdays not good as expected. Disappointing..
Pulled duck apricot croissant on lunch menu was really, really good. One of my best meals in Singapore.
Perfect eggs Benedict, excellent waffles, decent coffee and milkshakes. Place with a great vibe for your satisfactory weekend breakfast/brunch.
Food is good, but the service is three-toe sloth slow!

As noted by most, this place is priced more like a restaurant than a cafe. Food is tasty though. Flat white ($5.5) better than average too.No brunch on weekdays but also less hectic which is pleasant.
Although it's rather pricey (expect $40 / pax), the food is really nice!  Good ambience and service also. My fiancee and i ordered the Berkshire Pork and Beef ShortRibs. Very succulent and tasty!
Coffee n eggs benedict for brunch: perfection!
Eggs benedict, chocolate milkshake, and latte were all good. Their iPad/SMS notifications are the best implementation of a queue system I've seen so far. Overall, great experience and ambience!
Good eggs. Tastefully decorated
Restaurant opens at 9am but kitchen opens only at 9.30am.
Very good food with well balanced flavour profile.
Give their Baby Carrot dessert a try. Excellent combi of textures & flavors, certainly not just another cafe bar. Nice concept & ambience. Totally more than that! I reccomend! :)b
Food's good, well-executed & atmosphere's cosy. Meatlovers, go for the Welsh Rarebit. The Pork Cheek main is really tender, melts in your mouth. Overall a great dining experience.
Oh the waffles are to die for. The decor is old school and warm. The place is just a must visit at least once.
One word -> perfect

Delicious and best place for Brunch in Singapore!Their Truffle fries, Big Breakfast,Aglio Olio & Waffles are so yummy!Full review at  http://www.eatandtravelwithus.com/2013/12/brunch-at-symmetry-cafe/
Had dinner of kurobuta pork bourguignon and lamb shank. Pork was really tender and lamb tasted succulent without being gamey. Flat white was very smooth and soothing too.
Pork cheeks was very tender and great flavouring
a bit loud BGM but good ambience.
Such a perfect place for lunch or just a cup of coffee. Both the truffle fries and the croissants are absolute musts!🍟
Service is very poor. Don't choose outdoor seating as stuff will get blown into your food. It's nasty and very unsanitised.
Ajib lah pokok ny
Thumbs UP! 👍
The duck con-fee is delicious! Order this! Also heard the beef dishes are great. :D~~
Nice outdoor seating area. Brunch was good, waffles were better!
Snapper that is surprisingly good, refreshing. Want something light? U may try this!
Food was nice but too pricey
Get into their juices!
Good ambiance and nice coffee and dessert. Will come back again for the cold brew!
This place have a positive vibe, great servings, v tasty!😊
Jln Kubor is 2-way street, so u can get to cafe by Victoria St or North Bridge Rd. Free parking daily after 5pm & all day on Sundays
try a cuppa
A bit pricey. But worth it! good service great food. Eggs Benedict is a MUST TRY
Galaktisch geil ist der Baby Baramundi. Spannende Speisen und Drinks, super Atmosphäre und prei-Leistung stimmt 100 Mal mehr als in den ganzen poshen Restaurants.
the duck leg was nicely braised and tender. more homely than flashy but definitely tasty.
Don't be distraught if you can't get a seat inside. Having brunch al fresco is a breeze with the ample awning, natural shade from trees and fans. Try the Eggs Sur Le Plat. Spicy sausages with eggs.
Love their brunch. Their lunch is not bad also. Love the carbonara and I think they have the best truffle fries!
Deconstructed lemon tart was sublime
For brunch, enjoyed their eggs benedict, bruccolini & eggs, eggs sur le plat, waffles. Milkshakes r thick & tasty too. Mushroom carbonara had too much truffle oil. Coffee is always good :-)
Croissant, Symmetry Eggs, Latte, Lychee Mint
Healthy food options
2nd visit was a disappointment. Rather not comment.
The ambience is lovely, good music, vintage deco, and tasty food.
Retro & cosy ambient. Ordered my peninii (bread could toast a little crispier)& Soy latte (aromatic). Overall food (a little high on $$)& beverages is tasty n great👍👍 Will be back for another round
Apparently the q system at the entrance serves no purpose. A couple just walked in and sat down immediately after a table vacates. We did the same after waiting an hr, and they did not stop us.
Love milky stuffs? You will love the vanilla cereal milkshake. There's honey starss! Oooo
Excellent food. Service is rushed but lots of enthusiasm that shows willing hands for getting better. Great vibe :-D
Exp food, warm even the indoor seats but the killer blow is the expensive food. However, quality is good.
The owner of the restaurant has invested in a Slayer, one of the world’s most coveted espresso machines.
Truffle fries is a must. Minute steak is great. A tad too saltish but overall is great. Love the corned beef and hash. Difficult to find this simple dish nowadays.
Overrated... :( :( :(
not ur average cafe. rare 2 find gr8 food & coffee in 1 place! the simple Hokkaido scallops were deliciously smooth, tender & tasty. as was the shroom risotto. the coffee nv disappoints
Dinner here is somewhat pricey with small portions, but the quality of food is awesome. Loved the hokkaido scallop appetiser, beef short ribs and steak

Slowly becoming brunch's worst kept secret, and it's no surprise with their fantastic brunch menu! Coffee is great too - which is a plus as there aren't all that many brunch places that can offer both
Smart check-in system to get a table. Truffle fries!
Haven't been there for a while but the one time we've been there had great brunch food at the bar. Super hip and cozy ambience would try to go again soon.
This place became sort of legendary in the last years. Food is great and the coffee is in the top3 in Singapore.
The portobello with burrata and strawberry lemonade were very good. The Sunday roast left a lot to be desired - Yorkshire pudding had no gravy and steak was less than average quality.
super crowded... you will need a reservation and you will be requested to stick to your alloted time!
Quite expensive... Cant fill my stomache! :)
The most awesome egg Benedict ever!! Instead of poached egg, theirs is low temp egg, something like onsen egg, will definitely be back again (though I'm from m'sia) and they serve great cuppa!!
A must try are their truffle fries. Highly recommended.
Truffle fries! Anything on the menu is great, tried the foie gras burger and the pork cheek pasta!
We had best breakfast in Singapore here, however, the price tag is relatively expensive.. This is like standard European breakfast in Asian city. And if you like matcha, it isnt that great
Best bacon in Singapore! It was almost a religious experience. Truffle eggs were amazing in both taste and presentation. Tomato was deliciously sweet and sauteed mushrooms had great umami flavor.
Truffle fries must try
They've got this chaotically messy yet impeccably clean vibe going on. Delicious food and drinks too. The staff are snobby, but it kinda adds to the ambiance of the place.
The truffle toast is AMAZE-BALLS!!!
I also had their piccolo, espresso based was gd with a slight nutty profile towards the end,  milk was well textured, right temp. Overall a gd cuppa! :)
WiFi: openonmonday
Duck leg confit - crispy skin, tender meat. Comes with risotto, foie gras and mushrooms. Perfect!! All my favorite food in one dish!!
Pork cheek pasta... Very good!!
As stated among previous good tips, the pork cheek pasta n the coffee are divine :)
The duck! Friendly staff!
Steak burger is delicious. The music is a bit too loud.
Truffle fries is great!!!!!
The pork belly Croissant - had good flavour, good quality croissant made with butter instead of margarine! Pork was moist, eggs scrambled well ..The arugula salad was dressed well - not over done!!
truffle fries & pulled duck and apricot croissant
Very good coffee. Extensive brunch menu too. Symmetry egg sur le plat (bottom right) is awesome - Tunisian-like breakfast. Worth a revisit!
If you're there for Brunch and the kitchen isn't busy, they might agree to make a Croque Madame...which is awesome!!
good place for mid-size group gatherings
The best place to chill out...with friends...
Great coffee, really LOUD music!!! Bring earplugs.
Food was so rich to the point that it was almost disgusting. A few bites were actually disgusting. Overpriced, too.
The white tables outside make an ideal Instagram backdrop for your food! (Not recommended to sit outside when very warm or raining, for obvious reasons)
Adore the cutleries, interiors & cool looking slayer coffee machine. Enjoyed the coffee with Mr Ginger. :D
Awesome place to chill and catch up with friends for brunch! :)
Yum green tea latte
Definitely get their burgers and breakfast items.
The bottles are recycled ... Used and washed. I asked for a bottle (thought the size was cute) but turned down.
👍 for the Ham hock and pancetta steak. Meals here - be it Brekkie or dinner, always meet expectations.
Fantastic. Well recommend. We went for Mother's Day brunch. Did not disappoint.
Symmetry Benedict
The lamb tho... I wish I ordered the salad too! This place is great at night and with friends. 😀
Juicy pork belly croissant and yakult sake were lovely.
First time in this cafe. I was really excited as the good reviews led me here. Unfortunately, it was not as good as reviewed. The prices of the food are not as worth as the price. Coffee is alright.
Food princely. Pork pasta, chicken, duck leg are salty..  Potato fried ok.
Best truffle fries ever!! :)
Good brunch menu tho expensive. Ordered coffee (great) and squid (delicious). After 1 hr, mains still weren't ready so we cancelled. They graciously comped the coffee and squid.
Traffle fries is the best
Symmetry Egg Benedict is appetizing
Expensive, loud music if you're sitting outside, clientele is clearly there to see and be seen. But the food is good. Go if you feel like splurging on brunch.
With certs from Le Cordon Bleu, local chef Abby Lim helms the kitchen at this hidden gem in Kampong Glam.
Great brunch. Order the eggs Benedict.. You won't regret it, I ate every bite! Orange juice is also yummy
One of the better brunch cafés in SG, be ready to wait an hour or more for an indoor table. Truffle fries was just ok for me. Eggs Sur Le Plat was good.
Pricey - brunch for 2 (mains and drinks each) came up to $70!!!
Eggs Sur Le Plat (S$24) is delicious. Similar to eggs shakshoukha. Attentive service. Pretty expensive though. Fresh juice is S$10!
Their muzt have truffles fries (& am eating nonstop)
OK piccolo, cool vibe. Turns into a bar at night. The food is horrible - not a single vegetarian or healthy option unless you want to eat tones of sugar!
